      "rationale": "Mesh convergence studies were performed by all three teams. Refinement from baseline to twice the element density produced less than 3% change in all three QoIs. Richardson extrapolation applied to estimate discretization error contribution to total uncertainty budget."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver residuals documented and within acceptable tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Force and displacement residuals monitored throughout each nonlinear quasi-static analysis. Convergence tolerances of 1e-4 applied consistently. No convergence failures observed across the ensemble. Iterative solver error contribution estimated as negligible relative to other uncertainty sources."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented model setup review and independent verification of boundary conditions, material assignments, and loading.",
      "rationale": "Each modeling team conducted an independent internal review of model setup including boundary conditions, material property assignments, contact definitions, and loading protocol. Cross-team comparison of model inputs identified and resolved one discrepancy in load application point prior to final analyses."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
