      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification that model physics appropriately represent the dominant deformation and failure mechanisms for the COU.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear elastic-plastic continuum FEA with contact is judged appropriate for the dominant bending, contact, and yielding behavior of the pedicle screw-rod construct under ASTM F1717 loading. Bone substitute block modeled as rigid per ASTM F1717 protocol. Screw-rod interface modeled with frictional contact consistent with physical assembly."
    },
    {
